# Instalação

## Instalar NodeJs:

https://nodejs.org/en/download/ 

## Documentação

Entrar via browser no link abaixo para acessar a documentação:

```
    https://localhost:8443/automation-api/startHere.html
```

## Download Command Line Interface (CLI)

Entrar via browser no link abaixo para download:

```
    https://localhost:8443/automation-api/ctm-cli.tgz
```

## Instalar o CLI Control-M

No terminal, executar:

```
    npm -g install ctm-cli.tgz
```

## Testar a instalação CLI 

No terminal, executar:

```
    ctm
```

# Scripts

Entrar dentro da pasta control-m:

```
    cd control-m
```

ctm environment workbench::add

ctm environment set workbench

ctm environment add devEnvironment "https://localhost:8443/automation-api" emuser empassword 

ctm environment add devEnvironment2 "https://127.0.0.1:8443/automation-api" emuser empassword 

ctm environment set devEnvironment2


Rodar os scripts abaixo para começar as orquestrações:

```
    ctm run AutomationAPISampleFlow.json --interactive
```

```
    ctm run command-job.json --interactive
    ctm run status "761d4552-cf0f-405d-95f6-27ced9b28b46"
```